// Question: Have the function PowersofTwo(num) take the num parameter being passed which will be an integer
// and return the string true if it's a power of two. If it's not return the string false. For example if the
// input is 16 then your program should return the string true but if the input is 22 then the output should 
// be the string false. 

function PowersofTwo(num) { 
 var flag=0;
 while(flag === 0){
    flag = num % 2;
    num /=2;
 }
    
 if(num == 0.5)
    return "true";
 else
    return "false";
}
   
// keep this function call here 
// to see how to enter arguments in JavaScript scroll down
PowersofTwo(readline());           
